ing to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Cunedda ap Hywel was born about 1145, his father, Hywel ap Ieuaf of Trefeglwys, was 22 and his mother, Mawd verch Ieuan, was 39. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1145–":"umbes 1145–Surnud","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1150–1180":"1150–1180","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1108–Female":"1108–Surnud","1125":"1125","Abt 1145":"umbes 1145","1145":"1145","Abt 1147":"umbes 1147","1150":"1150","1108":"1108","1180":"1180","Arwestli, Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1145–":"noin 1145–Kuollut","1145–Male":"1145–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1150–1180":"1150–1180","1125–Male":"1125–Kuollut","1108–Female":"1108–Kuollut","1125":"1125","Abt 1145":"noin 1145","1145":"1145","Abt 1147":"noin 1147","1150":"1150","1108":"1108","1180":"1180","Arwestli, Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1145–":"environ 1145–Décédé","1145–Male":"1145–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1150–1180":"1150–1180","1125–Male":"1125–Décédé","1108–Female":"1108–Décédée","1125":"1125","Abt 1145":"environ 1145","1145":"1145","Abt 1147":"environ 1147","1150":"1150","1108":"1108","1180":"1180","Arwestli, Mont